replies.body:
1.5% of missing mana per five,  this has a very profound effect especially in the early game. take {{champion:45}} for example. hypothetical situation you just killed someone and used all of your mana. now lets say you have about 600 total mana and have a natural regen rate of 9. the 1.5% regen for missing mana is equal to nine. 18 per five then Veigar's passive (18 * 2.5 = 45) that is equal to 9 mana in one second, which decreases the amount of time you would be vulnerable to encounters with the enemy jungler as you make your way back to the tower.

The Cunning tree adds a huge amount of utility and most supports need to invest 12-18 points in it. But you to have an open mind to try new things, experiment, if you want to build Tri force on Shen, go do it (no, I don't do it) not everyone has to build a champion, Runes and Masteries the way you do, even if it is not meta. please watch the next five to 10 minutes of this video. https://youtube/VDiGkPAtups?t=8m21s . it'll give a better overlook for the cunning tree. (if the link doesn't work look up "Mastery introduction league of legends 2016") 

Never ever playing Shen support without having the ADC on Skype after what happened last time. {{item:3070}}
